ch orbital motion, combined\nwith the strong Doppler boosting of the approaching relativistic jet, produces\na sine-wave modulation in the flux density which easily fits the observations.\nGiven the rapidly-developing field of gravitational wave experiments with\npulsar timing arrays, closer counterparts to PKS~2131$-$021 and searches using\nthe techniques we have developed are strongly motivated. These results\nconstitute a compelling demonstration that the phenomenology, not the theory,\nmust provide the lead in this field.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Nov 2021 18:00:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 24 Jan 2022 11:05:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-02"}
