rier during the Heyrovsky reaction is about 10.34 -\n10.79 kcal/mol, indicating an exceptional electrocatalyst for HER. The Tafel\nslope is lower in the case of 2D monolayer Mn-MoS$_2$ material due to the\noverlap of the s-orbital of the hydrogen and d-orbitals of the Mn atoms\nappeared in the HOMO and LUMO transition states (TS1 and TS2) of both the\nVolmer and Heyrovsky reaction steps.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Nov 2021 09:42:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 6 Jan 2022 18:39:26 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 18 Jun 2022 13:33:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-22"}
