icant non-gyrotropic momentum flux component that is higher\nthan that of the second mass-loaded case. Mass loading is not a sufficient\nexplanation for the distribution functions and momentum flux tensor in the\nfirst case, and so we assume this is evidence of bow shock formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Nov 2021 12:20:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 18 Feb 2022 12:47:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-27"}
